    • Method Detail

      • getInverseKinematicFromFrameAndRedundancy

        com.kuka.device.common.JointPosition getInverseKinematicFromFrameAndRedundancy(com.kuka.geometry.Frame frame,
                                                                               com.kuka.geometry.LoadData loadData)
        Calculates the JointPosition value of the given frame under the flange of the robot (inverse kinematics).
        Parameters:
        frame - The flange frame for which the inverse kinematics is requested.
        loadData - Description of load attached to the flange. This load data is used in the kinematics calculation. However, it only has an effect if absolute accuracy is available for this robot.
        Returns:
        The result of the calculation from the controller.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the specified frame does not contain redundancy information

      • getForwardKinematics

        com.kuka.device.common.Pose getForwardKinematics(com.kuka.device.common.JointPosition joints,
                                                 com.kuka.geometry.LoadData loadData)
        Calculates the Pose of the robot for the given joint position (forward kinematics).
        Parameters:
        joints - The joint position for which the forward kinematics calculation is requested.
        loadData - Description of load attached to the flange. This load data is used in the kinematics calculation. However, it only has an effect if absolute accuracy is available for this robot IAbsoluteAccuracy.isAbsoluteAccuracyEnabled().
        Returns:
        Pose of the robot flange corresponding to the given joint position. Transformations in the returned Pose object are the coordinate system of the base of the robot (SpatialObject.getRootFrame())

      • parseCommandedRedundancy

        com.kuka.geometry.IRedundancyCollection parseCommandedRedundancy(Message message)
        Parses the given Message for commanded redundancy DFEs, and constructs the commanded IRedundancyCollection.
        Parameters:
        message - the message that contains the commanded redundancy information.
        Returns:
        the commanded IRedundancyCollection of the robot.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the message does not contain the expected redundancy information.

        Returns:

      • getRedundancyDFENames

        List<String> getRedundancyDFENames()
        Gets all redundancy related DFE names of the robot.

        It can be used to compose complex DFE requests.

        Returns:
        a list of all redundancy related DFE names of the robot.
        See Also:
        SSRFactory#requestDFEData}
